  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  who have idiopathic scoliosis, showing at Cobb's angle over 20 degrees,less than 45 on
             X-ray

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who underwent spinal surgery

          -  Patients with spinal scoliosis due to cerebral palsy, muscle paralysis, polio,
             congenital spinal abnormalities

          -  Patients observed with Cobb's angle less than 20 degrees, over 45 degrees

          -  Patients complaining of acute low back pain

          -  Patients with cognitive impairment, severe mental illness, and inability to
             communicate
      </textblock>
